1.00	John_Baddely	John Baddeley (actor)	Edward John Baddeley (born 16 July 1933 Bridgnorth, Shropshire, England) is a British actor. Apart from his work in the theatre in the provinces and the West End, he is also notable for his work with the BBC and as voice-over artist. Credits include Top Hat and Zip in TUGS, his narration work as Winston Churchill in a 2003 documentary series, and for roles in shows such as Z-Cars, Doctor at Large and in Shakespeare: The Animated Tales. He has also worked as a voice coach and director for Teddington Theatre Club. His autobiography Double Take was published in 2009.	
